      "comment": "HOT NANU (2) was in the placings last time but shapes well for this on his blistering win the start prior, getting around Sandown over 515m in 29.23. Rates a top chance if runs up to time two back. PAW MANTRA (8) is long overdue for a win and in super consistent form, jumping from this box to place last time at this track (26.68), making it four straight minors. Harder here but expected to feature again. TREBLE BEERS (1) failed to come into contention last start after settling well back at The Meadows, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at The Meadows (30.18) beating Crackerjack Kev in a Grade 5 FIN on January 31. Some good form is emerging from his last run. One of the better chances. BROTHER DOOM (3) did the right thing for favourite backers last time - another big run is on the cards.",
